==English==
===Etymology===
From [[piss]] + [[mire]] ‘ant’, named from the smell of an anthill.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'pɪsmʌɪə/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pismire|pismires}}
# ''(obsolete except in dialects)'' an [[ant]]
#:*'''Late C14''': He is as angry as a '''pissemyre''', / Þogh þat he have al þat he kan desire — Geoffrey Chaucer, ''The Summoner's Tale''
#:*'''1993''': We are scurrying emmets or '''pismires''' with our sad little comedies. — Anthony Burgess, ''A Dead Man in Deptford''

